He acquainted the citizens with the condition of affairs within and without the city, defended himself from a double charge, busily circulated by his enemieS, that Catiline if guilty had been allowed to escape, if innocent had been driven into exile, encouraged those who were anxious over the result of the apprehended war, and finally tried to frighten from their purposes the conspirators that were in the city.
